{
  "texts": [
    "While these terms are unsuitable for end-users, they can meet the \"understandable\" criterion for developers, even without abstractions.",
    "Retrieval: We retrieved tens of thousands of NLP interpretability papers using the Semantic Scholar API and by searching queries such as NLP interpretability (a full list of queries is provided in Box D.1).",
    "We kept only papers whose titles or abstracts contained at least one NLP keyword (e.g., NLP, LLM, BERT; see Box D.2) and one interpretability keyword (e.g., interpretability, XAI, explanation; see Box D.3).",
    "This search and selection process yielded 14,676 papers.",
    "Annotation and Filtering: For determining the relevancy of the papers and annotating them, we employed an LLM (gemini-1.5pro-preview-0514) and used the zero-shot prompt provided in Box D.4."
  ]
}